news.title: China urges banks to support property sector after mortgage boycott
news.para: The China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission (CBIRC) told the official industry newspaper on Sunday that banks should meet developers' financing needs where reasonable.

news.title: Construction waste plant still a dream for Ludhiana smart city
news.para: ​The project is planned under smart city mission, and officials claimed that work was going to start at the site in Dhandhari soon.

news.title: Delhi court upholds conviction of Ansal brothers for evidence tampering
news.para: Besides Ansals, the court had also awarded 7-year jail terms to former court staff Dinesh Chand Sharma and two others -- P P Batra and Anoop Singh -- and had imposed a fine of three lakh rupees each on them.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's profit falls 25% to Rs 52 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: However, revenue from operation increased 6.10 per cent to Rs 589.89 crore during the quarter under review from Rs 555.94 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Assam: 71 houses demolished on second day in Karimganj
news.para: The administration carried out the drive to clear atleast 1,200 bighas of government and ceiling-surplus land in Ichabeel tea estate, owned by the state-run Assam Tea Corporation (ATC), and neighbouring areas which were encroached by the families without valid documents.

news.title: Prestige Group's sales bookings jump four-fold to Rs 3,012 crore
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Bengaluru-based Prestige Group said it has registered sales of Rs 3,012.1 crore, of which the Mumbai region has contributed Rs 737.8 crore.

news.title: Patta camps to follow ward-wise survey: Rajasthan minister
news.para: Khachariyawas was addressing a meeting at the secretariat on Sunday to resolve the problems being faced regarding the leases being given under the campaign in areas under Jaipur Municipal Corporation-Heritage.

news.title: L&T Realty to develop three projects worth Rs 8,000 crore in Mumbai region
news.para: The South Mumbai residential project will be developed over a land parcel of five acres and will have 50 storey twin towers. The Thane project will be developed on a six acres land parcel.

news.title: Nashik civic body to evacuate residents of dilapidated homes at Kazigadi
news.para: NMC officials said they are taking such measures in view of the monsoon as there are possibilities of landslides at the old hillock due to ongoing rain.

news.title: Greater Noida's sector Techzone 4: Home to 5,000 families, but not a single footpath for them
news.para: Apart from that, residents demand redress from broken, encroached roads, untended C&D waste and garbage, stray animals on the road and lack of sanitation, especially in the market area.

news.title: Jodhpur administration to monitor camps to speed up patta delivery
news.para: “The monitoring cell will supervise the camps in order to ensure that the target of pattas to be issued at the camps could be achieved,” said an administrative official.

news.title: PMRDA to assess 12 proposals from citizens for its voluntary town planning projects
news.para: The self-proposed town planning schemes have been initiated by groups of citizens who have a minimum of 100 acres of land and want to develop it as a town planning scheme with the help of the PMRDA.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government eyes big in energy-saving in housing scheme
news.para: The state government will supply cost-effective energy efficient appliances (four LED bulbs, two LED tube Lights and two energy efficient fans) to each beneficiary of the housing scheme.

news.title: Roads in Ghaziabad townships are a 'civic disaster'
news.para: The innumerable potholes and craters cause waterlogging even at the lightest spell of rain and pose a grave risk to commuters not used to a bumpy ride in these areas.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board's survey of allotted flats delayed due to rain
news.para: Such flats cannot be sold, sub-let, transferred and handed over to other persons. According to the board, there are unconfirmed reports of some allottees selling, transferring their flats illegally, which may attract case for fraud, cheating etc.
